<subSubSection pageId="96" pageNumber="374" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="96.[787,1380,927,1350]" pageId="96" pageNumber="374">
Three subspecies (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mearns" authorityYear="1896" box="[1075,1193,1049,1074]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Onychomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="96" pageNumber="374" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="arenicola">arenicola</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Merriam" authorityYear="1904" box="[1223,1297,1049,1074]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Cansumys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="96" pageNumber="374" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="canus">canus</taxonomicName>
, and surrufus) were removed from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Coues" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[1229,1372,1088,1113]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Onychomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="96" pageNumber="374" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="torridus">O. torridus</taxonomicName>
, when 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mearns" authorityYear="1896" box="[878,1033,1119,1152]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Onychomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="96" pageNumber="374" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="arenicola">O. arenicola</taxonomicName>
was elevated to full species status. Ten subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
